\
First, connect to the server using a DB that *does* exist, usually `postgres`:\
\
```bash\
psql "postgresql://postgres:mypwd@127.0.0.1:5434/postgres"\
```\
Then list databases:\
\
```sql\
\\l\
```\
Pick the database you actually want to use (for example, maybe it\'92s `nexusdev`, `nexus`, or something else), then update your env:\
\
```env\
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:mypwd@127.0.0.1:5434/ACTUAL_DB_NAME"\
```\
and test:\
\
```bash\
psql "postgresql://postgres:mypwd@127.0.0.1:5434/ACTUAL_DB_NAME"\
```\
