\
## 2. Create `nexusdev-v2` and keep your URL\
\
If you *want* the DB to be named `nexusdev-v2`, just create it.\
\
Connect to `postgres`:\
\
```bash\
psql "postgresql://postgres:mypwd@127.0.0.1:5434/postgres"\
```\
Then:\
\
```sql\
CREATE DATABASE "nexusdev-v2";\
\\q\
```\
Now your existing URL will work:\
\
```bash\
psql "postgresql://postgres:mypwd@127.0.0.1:5434/nexusdev-v2"\
```\
and your `DATABASE_URL` doesn\'92t need to change.\
